SMI Drops on Debt Downgrades for Greece, Portugal; UBS, Swiss Re Retreat

-- B y   W i l l   H a d f i e l d
-- 
2011-03-29T14:03:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-29/swiss-stocks-retreat-on-portugal-greece-downgrades-ubs-falls.html
Swiss stocks dropped as Greece and
Portugal’s credit ratings were cut by  Standard & Poor’s , and
consumer demand in Switzerland fell for a second month.  Swiss Reinsurance Co. dropped 1.6 percent after saying the
cost of natural disasters rose 76 percent last year.  UBS AG (UBSN) 
declined 2 percent.  The Swiss Market Index of the biggest and most actively
traded companies lost 0.3 percent to 6,337.17 at 4:01 p.m. in
Zurich. The measure has still rebounded 5.3 percent since March
16 as investors speculated that Japan will contain its nuclear
crisis and as the U.S., the U.K. and France took control of
Libya’s airspace. The broader Swiss Performance Index also fell
0.3 percent today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Hadfield at 
 whadfield@bloomberg.net  